# Security & RLS Rules

## Pre-Deployment Security Checklist

### Supabase RLS
- [ ] Every table in `public` schema has RLS enabled
- [ ] No policy uses `user_metadata` (user-editable, not trusted)
- [ ] UPDATE policies have both `USING` and `WITH CHECK`
- [ ] SECURITY DEFINER functions explicitly justified
- [ ] Views use `security_invoker = true`
- [ ] Storage: private buckets require auth

### Authentication
- [ ] JWT access tokens short-lived (1 hour max)
- [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage
- [ ] Auth state checked in middleware for protected routes

### Multi-Tenancy
- [ ] Every DB query scoped by `tenant_id`
- [ ] No endpoint returns cross-tenant data
- [ ] Subdomain slug validated against tenant table

### Payments
- [ ] Razorpay `key_secret` NEVER in client code
- [ ] HMAC verification on every webhook
- [ ] Payment amounts validated server-side
- [ ] Idempotent webhook processing

### API Security
- [ ] Rate limiting on auth endpoints (5 req/min)
- [ ] Rate limiting on OTP endpoints (3 req/15 min)
- [ ] No stack traces in production errors
- [ ] CORS: `*.cafecanvas.bar` only

## Known Vulnerability

🚨 `payment_integrations` table — RLS allows any authenticated staff to read Razorpay secrets.
Fix: restrict SELECT to `owner`/`manager` roles only.
